cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.MM 

This paper deals with machine learning models and their bias towards certain communities, specifically racial bias in gender recognition systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of an adversarially trained autoencoder model, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of bias in machine learning models, which is a topic covered in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper deals with human faces, which is a topic covered in cs.MM (Multimedia).
